==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English [[mok]], [[muk]], borrowed from Old Norse [[myki]] 'dung'.

===Pronunciation===
*''US:'' {{IPA|/mʌk/}}, {{SAMPA|/mVk/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌk|-ʌk]]

===Noun===
'''muck''' (''uncountable'')
# slimy mud
# soft or slimy [[manure]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[muta]] (''more solid''), [[lieju]] (''more running'')

====Derived terms====
* [[muck about]]
* [[muck around]]
* [[muck in]]
* [[muck out]]
* [[mucker]]
* [[muckraker]]
* [[mucky]]
* [[muck spreader]]

